# web-admin UI Imports (Mandatory)

When writing or suggesting **UI code in web-admin**:

1. **Use Cmx design system only.** Import from `@ui/primitives`, `@ui/feedback`, `@ui/overlays`, `@ui/forms`, `@ui/data-display`, `@ui/navigation`. Do **not** use `@ui/compat` (removed).
2. **Use the exact import snippets from `web-admin/.clauderc`** in the `ui_components` section for buttons, inputs, cards, dialogs, alerts, selects, tabs, etc. When generating a component (e.g. Button, Card, Dialog), copy the corresponding snippet from `.clauderc` so imports are correct.
3. **Use `cmxMessage` / `useMessage` from `@ui/feedback`** for all applicable user-facing success/error/warning/info/confirm feedback. See `docs/dev/rules/cmx-message.md` and `.cursor/rules/cmx-message.mdc`. Do not add new legacy `showSuccessToast` / raw `toast()` / `alert()` call sites.
4. **Run `npm run build`** in web-admin after UI changes; ESLint and TypeScript will fail on invalid or restricted imports.

Restricted (will fail build/lint): `@ui/compat`, `@/components/ui`, `@/components/ui/*`.

Full conventions: `.cursor/rules/frontendstandards.mdc` (section "web-admin/.clauderc (AI Hints)"), `docs/dev/ui-migration-guide.md`.

**TypeScript / Cmx pitfalls (tsc):** When editing `web-admin/`, also follow `.cursor/rules/web-admin-typecheck-patterns.mdc` (action-result narrowing, `CmxButton`/`Badge`/`CmxSummaryMessage`/`CmxDialog`, RHF+Zod, etc.).
